headline: Bullish (BLSH): Assessing Valuation as Record Q3 Results and Major Backers Meet Market Skepticism
summary: Bullish (BLSH) just posted record third-quarter revenue and swung to a profit, reversing its loss from last year after launching crypto options and expanding into U.S. spot trading under a new license. These operational milestones have brought substantial growth, even as the stock has struggled to find traction in a cautious market. See our latest analysis for Bullish. headline: Bitcoin ETFs Hit Record $11.5 Billion Volume as Most Investors Slip Into Losses
summary: US spot Bitcoin ETFs logged a record $11.5 billion in trading volume, led by BlackRock’s IBIT, which alone generated $8 billion in turnover.

headline: Investors Clamor for a Peek Behind the Private Markets Curtain
summary: Wall Street wants to sell data on private markets, where pensions and colleges pay hefty fees and receive scant information.
